$interpreted: Pang: Yao!?
Chiyuki: (It's him!)
Turtle Chieftain: It's him! That psycho who hit me!
Wolf Chieftain: Wait a second... isn't he that old Tiger Tribe prince!?
Surprised Audience: What!? You mean, that traitor that wanted to bring down the Alliance!?
Scared Audience: I thought he died! How could he be here!?
Maeok: Silence!
Maeok: I don't know how you're still alive.
Maeok: But you are a criminal here, and now you're back here bringing shame to our holy tournament!? What is the meaning of this!?
Yao: How dare you question me? You are not worthy.
Shun: Arbiter, do not waste your time on this one!
Shun: Come, apprehend him!
Pang: Yao, let go!
Yao: Let go? Do you have the right to say that? You're not even a real contestant, after all.
Yao: Are you all blind? Look closely!

Yao: I have the real holy talisman! Me!
I am the true Tiger Tribe contestant!
Shun: The holy talisman!? But... how!?
Toyokuni: ...That is the holy talisman, no doubt about it.
Tapir Chieftain: W-What's going on?
Maeok: Did that belong to... General Yu?
Shun: Huh?
Maeok: You're right... we were always fixated on Pang, not realizing there was another who knew General Yu's only weak point...
Maeok: ...Someone who should have been a ghost, long ago.
Yao: Still trying to cover that up?
Yao: You all know more than anyone that I've been alive all this time.
Surprised Audience: What!? The Alliance has known this whole time!?
Turtle Chieftain: Now, now, don't panic! Why believe a word this fugitive says!?
Wolf Chieftain: He ran for his life, didn't he? Now he's back, trying to clear his name! Right, Arbiter Maeok? General Shun?
Pang: You really do have it... the holy talisman...
Pang: Then it was you... You killed General Yu.
Pang: What's your endgame here, Yao!?
Yao: I want to win this tournament and become the arbiter, of course. I want to topple this corrupt regime.
Tindoiimu: You want to be the arbiter? So much that you would risk your life to come out of hiding?
Yao: What do you think?
Tindoiimu: ...I suppose you're right, this might have been the only way.
Tindoiimu: Given who you are, your only choice is to pressure the Alliance like this, right at the very end.
Tindoiimu: Even if you do have the holy talisman...
Tindoiimu: If you showed up at the beginning, they might have just had you locked up, or worse...
Yao: Hmph, you're pretty smart... for a bug.
Pang: So, your plan was to let me compete, rise the ranks... then swoop in and take it?
Pang: That's what you meant... when you said you'd need me...
Chiyuki: (That's what Yao meant, back at the cold springs!)
Pang: And for this goal, you even went so far as to kill General Yu...
Yao: Quit acting surprised. You know how much blood was on his hands.
Yao: You know he was the type to get arrogant, greedy, surrounded by those who admire him.
Yao: That kind of person... as long as they're in a position of power, they leave death in their wake.
Yao: No exceptions.
Pang: Yao... you really want to be the arbiter?
Pang: You...
Panther Chieftain: Hold on, if that traitor has the real Tiger Tribe holy talisman, then what is the other tiger holding?
Pang: This is...
Seahorse Chieftain: Answer the question!
Pang: ...I am holding the Capybara Tribe's holy talisman.
Scared Audience: The Capybara Tribe? They aren't even a part of this tournament anymore!
Scared Audience: I don't think he was accepted here by the Keeper of the Udumbara at all!
Young Audience: But wait, I thought everything that happened was the Udumbara's will? Then... how would he have let Pang rise so far in the ranks!?
Surprised Audience: And then, what about that traitor's holy talisman!?
Maeok: Chieftain...
Tapir Chieftain: Ah... I...
